<DOC><DOCNO> AP880809-0069 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-09-88 1106EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w PM-SpaceCommittee     08-09 0153</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Space Committee,150</SECOND><HEAD>Corporate Leaders Appointed To Space Advisory Committee</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Commerce Secretary C. William Verity hasannounced the establishment of the Commercial Space AdvisoryCommittee to recommend ways to increase U.S. business presence inspace ventures and activities.   ``The U.S. needs to forge a stronger link between our vastscience and technology resources and U.S. corporations andentrepreneurs ... to ensure an economic environment where U.S.space commerce can thrive,'' Verity said in a statement Monday.   The 15-member panel, composed of representatives from industry,government and higher education, is scheduled to makerecommendations to the administration by the end of October, whenits authorization expires.   All but two of the committee members represent corporations nottraditionally associated with space ventures. Ed Hood, vicepresident of General Electric Co., will serve as chairman of thegroup which also includes governors Bob Martinez of Florida andJohn D. Waihee of Hawaii.</TEXT></DOC>